The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Dec. 30: The country?s balance of payment (BoP) situation improved and forex reserves increased to $143.1 billion till the first half of 2005-06 despite doubling of trade deficit. The improvement in the BoP situation comes after a robust capital inflow of $18.72 billion in the form of FDI ($2.3 billion), FII ($5.1 billion) and ECBs ($2.75 billion). 

 Mumbai, Dec. 30: The rupee today appreciated sharply against the greenback and gained 13 paise to end the day at 45.04 per dollar following heavy inflows of the US currency from sales by foreign banks amid lack of import buying.

 Mumbai, Dec. 30: Aftek Infosys Ltd has acquired a 100 per cent stake in the Munich-based Arexera Information Technologies GMBH after picking up the remaining 51 per cent of the German company.

 Mumbai, Dec. 30: The government today clarified that the proposed 2 per cent health cess for the poor won?t be an additional burden on taxpayers, but a levy on the central taxes.

 New Delhi, Dec. 30: Hutch has launched a pre-paid recharge card of Rs 2,000, giving full talktime to its subscribers with a validity of one year. AirTel is offering discount on international calls for one week.




